    explanation: "Fine-tuned models in Bedrock require Provisioned Throughput to be deployed for inference. Provisioned Throughput creates a dedicated model unit (MU) with reserved capacity. Access is controlled via IAM resource policies on the provisioned model ARN. On-demand API access is not available for fine-tuned models without provisioning. ✓ (a) Provisioned Throughput is the required and only deployment path for fine-tuned Bedrock models; it creates a dedicated model ARN that IAM resource-based policies can scope to specific teams, principals, or accounts. ✗ (b) Bedrock fine-tuned model weights remain within the Bedrock service and cannot be exported to S3 or deployed to SageMaker; the fine-tuning output is a Bedrock-managed custom model, not portable model artifacts. ✗ (c) Fine-tuned models are not automatically available via the Bedrock on-demand API; the on-demand API serves only pre-trained foundation models, and custom fine-tuned models require explicit Provisioned Throughput purchase before they can serve inference traffic. ✗ (d) Deploying a fine-tuned model as a Bedrock Agent with a custom system prompt is not a valid deployment pattern; Bedrock Agents use a foundation model as their orchestration engine and do not provide a mechanism to specify a custom fine-tuned model variant as the agent base.",
